{
  "stem": "2002.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "His mind was more towards religion than to feed the children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was times, as I remember, when it came to a holiday where the neighbors were cookin' for Passover, or Rosh Hashanah, Yom Kippur-- especially Passover.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I remember distinctly that my mother and my sister would put [? rocks ?] in the pots that the smoke, the steam to go out the windows-- through a window, that the people should think that we have also food for Passover, which we didn't have it.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The fact is, I just looked in a book.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I saw a man-- I forgot his name now.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he would help us out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But there wasn't too many rich people that they could help.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So as much if we could get help, we got it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the interesting story is that we were five brothers and three sisters.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, when we grew up, you would never knew that we come from a family that poor, because every one of us grew up to be-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] how to explain?",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One of the nicest people in the town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I have to tell, also, at times I used to work for a Polish man in the farm.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Polish man was an alcoholic.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he took me many time to his place where he keeps the wheat because his wife had the key.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He couldn't get in, because she knew he was alcoholic.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he went in by takin' off some pieces of wood, he could slide in.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he would give it to me to sell it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then when I sold it, I gave him the money, he bought liquor.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
